<opener>
<lb/><dateline rend="right"> <add place="above" rend="center" hand="U">10</add> <add place="above" rend="right" hand="#U">29</add><placeName><placeName>50 Albermarle <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></placeName> 
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="U">[not indexed]</add><placeName>London</placeName></placeName> 
<lb/><date when="1858-01-28">28 January 
<lb/>1858</date></dateline>
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear Boy</salute>
</opener>

<lb/><p>If it will not 
<lb/>be deemed an intrusion
<lb/>for one who has trod
<lb/>the path of life <w>some -
<lb break="no"/>what</w> ahead of you
<lb/>to address a few
<lb/>loving words to a
<lb/>person whom he has

	<pb facs="liv_001198_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>never seen I would
<lb/>say that one of the
<lb/>greatest comforts I
<lb/>have enjoyed in my
<lb/>chequered course
<lb/>has flowed from
<lb/>obedience to the command<!-- Should we correct this sentence by supplying a full stop? -->
<lb/>Commit thy way unto the
<lb/>Lord, trust also in
<lb/>him, and he shall
<lb/>bring it to pass. This
<lb/>resource has been
<lb/>present to my mind

	<pb facs="liv_001198_0003" n="0003"/>
 <add place="above" rend="right" hand="#U">30</add>
<lb/>in every step of my
<lb/>wanderings, I did 
<lb/>commit my way to
<lb/>him and he has guided
<lb/>me well. I never
<lb/>say much about my
<lb/>inward emotions,
<lb/>and have an inveterate
<lb/>hatred to count, but
<lb/>having derived so
<lb/>much internal strength
<lb/>from "acknowledging 
<lb/>the Lord in all my
<lb/>ways" I have thought

	<pb facs="liv_001198_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>from what your
<lb/>good Mama said to
<lb/>me about you, that
<lb/>in beginning the path
<lb/>of life you would
<lb/>like to know this
<lb/>little experience, and
<lb/>may the Lord guide
<lb/>you and preserve 
<lb/>you from all evil
<lb/><choice><sic>untill</sic><corr>until</corr></choice> through infinite
<lb/>mercy we meet in
<lb/>Heaven - yours be
</p>

<closer rend="right">
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed> 
</closer>


            </div>
